            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>China/China Mainland eSIM – usable only in mainland China.</li>
              <li>China–Hong Kong–Macau eSIM – covers mainland China, Hong Kong, and Macau (regional package).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- FAQ 2 -->
        <details class="faqItem border border-primary bg-neutral">
          <summary
            class="
              flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer
              px-[10px] py-[5px] md:py-[10px] text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-medium text-primary
              list-none leading-[20px] md:leading-relaxed
            "
          >
            <span>How long is the active period?</span>

            <span class="faqChevron inline-flex items-center justify-center w-[34px] h-[34px] transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="text-primary">
                <path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>

          <div class="px-[20px] pb-[20px] text-primary leading-relaxed text-[16px] space-y-4">
            <p>
              eSIM products are available in various durations, from 1 day up to 30 days, depending on the selected
              package.
            </p>

            <div>
              <p class="font-bold">Important note:</p>
              <p>
                The eSIM must be scanned within a certain period (e.g. within 30 days after purchase). If not scanned
                within this time, it will expire and cannot be used.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- FAQ 3 -->
        <details class="faqItem border border-primary bg-neutral">
          <summary
            class="
              flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer
              px-[10px] py-[5px] md:py-[10px] text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-medium text-primary
              list-none leading-[20px] md:leading-relaxed
            "
          >
            <span>How do I activate the eSIM?</span>

            <span class="faqChevron inline-flex items-center justify-center w-[34px] h-[34px] transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="text-primary">
                <path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>

          <div class="px-[20px] pb-[20px] text-primary leading-relaxed text-[16px] space-y-4">
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>After purchase, you will receive a QR code via email.</li>
              <li>Scan the QR code via Settings → Add eSIM on your phone.</li>
              <li>
                It is recommended to scan the QR code before arriving in China for smoother access (including TikTok
                access).
              </li>
            </ul>

            <p>
              <span class="font-medium">Tip:</span> Make sure your device supports eSIM by checking the EID in your
              phone’s settings.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- FAQ 4 -->
        <details class="faqItem border border-primary bg-neutral">
          <summary
            class="
              flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer
              px-[10px] py-[5px] md:py-[10px] text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-medium text-primary
              list-none leading-[20px] md:leading-relaxed
            "
          >
            <span>Does it support calls or SMS?</span>

            <span class="faqChevron inline-flex items-center justify-center w-[34px] h-[34px] transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="text-primary">
                <path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>

          <div class="px-[20px] pb-[20px] text-primary leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
            <p>All products sold are data-only internet packages. Voice calls and SMS are not supported.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- FAQ 5 -->
        <details class="faqItem border border-primary bg-neutral">
          <summary
            class="
              flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer
              px-[10px] py-[5px] md:py-[10px] text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-medium text-primary
              list-none leading-[20px] md:leading-relaxed
            "
          >
            <span>Can I use hotspot / tethering?</span>

            <span class="faqChevron inline-flex items-center justify-center w-[34px] h-[34px] transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="text-primary">
                <path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>

          <div class="px-[20px] pb-[20px] text-primary leading-relaxed text-[16px]">
            <p>Yes, hotspot/personal tethering is supported on most eSIM packages.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- FAQ 6 -->
        <details class="faqItem border border-primary bg-neutral">
          <summary
            class="
              flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer
              px-[10px] py-[5px] md:py-[10px] text-[16px] md:text-[18px] font-medium text-primary
              list-none leading-[20px] md:leading-relaxed
            "
          >
            <span>What should I know about the network & technology?</span>

            <span class="faqChevron inline-flex items-center justify-center w-[34px] h-[34px] transition-transform duration-200">
              <svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="text-primary">
                <path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>

          <div class="px-[20px] pb-[20px] text-primary leading-relaxed text-[16px] space-y-4">
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>
                SIM cards and eSIMs operate on 4G LTE networks (some packages support 5G, depending on device and
                service availability).
              </li>
              <li>
                APN settings are usually <span class="font-medium">mobile</span> /
                <span class="font-medium">cmLink</span> / <span class="font-medium">cmlink</span>, depending on the
                purchased product.
              </li>
            </ul>

            <p>
              <span class="font-medium">Note:</span> Some apps (e.g. TikTok, ChatGPT, Mobile Legends) may not be
              accessible depending on the package and network. Please check the product description before purchase.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <style>
      #shopify-section-{{ sid }} summary::-webkit-details-marker { display:none; }
      #shopify-section-{{ sid }} summary::marker { content:""; }

      /* rotate icon when open */
      #shopify-section-{{ sid }} details[open] .faqChevron {
        transform: rotate(180deg);
      }

      /* open animation */
      #shopify-section-{{ sid }} details > div {
        animation: faqFadeIn 180ms ease;
      }
      @keyframes faqFadeIn {
        from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-6px); }
        to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
      }
    </style>

    <script>
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        const root = document.getElementById('shopify-section-{{ sid }}');
        if (!root) return;

        const wrap = root.querySelector('#faqWrap-{{ sid }}');
        if (!wrap) return;

        const detailsList = Array.from(wrap.querySelectorAll('details.faqItem'));
        if (!detailsList.length) return;

        // Default: close all
        detailsList.forEach((d) => d.removeAttribute('open'));

        // Only one open at a time
        detailsList.forEach((d) => {
          d.addEventListener('toggle', () => {
            if (!d.open) return;
            detailsList.forEach((other) => {
              if (other !== d) other.removeAttribute('open');
            });
          });
        });
      });
    </script>
  </section>
</div>

